Ad Text:
AWS Data Engineer – Databricks | Technology & Change Consultancy | Melbourne | ~$800/day

A leading technology, data, and change consultancy is seeking an experienced AWS Data Engineer with strong Databricks capability to support a major client program. This is a Melbourne-based hybrid contract offering around $800/day, working on large-scale, cloud-driven modernisation initiatives.

The Role You’ll help shape and deliver cloud-first data engineering solutions on AWS, leveraging Databricks, Delta Lake, and modern engineering practices. You’ll work closely with cross-functional teams to design, build, and optimise scalable data platforms across a high-impact transformation program.

What You’ll Do
Design, build & maintain AWS-native data pipelines using Databricks, PySpark, SQL, Delta Lake
Develop and optimise ETL/ELT workflows for both streaming and batch workloads
Embed best practices across data modelling, quality, testing, CI/CD, governance, and security
Partner with architects, engineers, and stakeholders to deliver fit-for-purpose, scalable solutions
Drive performance tuning, monitoring, and ongoing platform improvements
Contribute to the consultancy’s engineering patterns, frameworks, and reusable components
Tech Stack / Experience Needed
Strong hands-on experience with AWS (Glue, Lambda, Step Functions, S3, IAM, EMR/ECS, etc.)
Deep capability with Databricks (PySpark, SQL, notebooks, jobs, Delta Lake)
Experience with CI/CD, containerisation, and IaC (Terraform/CDK)
Solid software engineering fundamentals – testing, version control, clean code
Familiarity with data governance, cataloguing, lineage tools
Ability to operate effectively in consulting or fast-paced delivery environments
Strong communication and stakeholder engagement skills
Why This Contract?
Well-regarded consultancy focused on technology, data, and organisational change
Opportunity to work across a major modernisation program with a modern AWS/Databricks stack
Hybrid working model (Melbourne) with flexibility
Competitive ~$800/day engagement
Influence engineering approaches and deliver high-impact cloud solutions

Our client, a major Australian organisation undergoing significant digital and cloud transformation, is seeking a Monitoring & Observability Engineer to help build and enhance end-to-end visibility across a new cloud-based Sort Management platform. You’ll work closely with delivery teams, architects and vendors to uplift reliability, performance and service transparency across critical business systems.

6 month contract + potential extensions 
Located in Burnley
3 days in office each week
Leading Australian Organisation 

About the role

Develop, implement and maintain APM, logging and monitoring solutions (New Relic, Sumo Logic, ServiceNow ITOM).
Define and refine SLIs/SLOs and drive service reliability and operational readiness.
Support incident investigation, RCA and improvement of service performance.
Contribute to the observability roadmap and uplift best practices across multiple teams.
Collaborate with stakeholders and vendors on configuration, integration and support tasks.
Maintain documentation, follow change processes and provide occasional after-hours support.

About you

3+ years’ experience in monitoring, observability, operations, DevOps or SRE roles.
Strong hands-on experience with APM and logging tools (New Relic, AppDynamics, DataDog, Dynatrace, Sumo Logic, Splunk).
Experience in large-scale cloud or hybrid enterprise environments.
Excellent analytical, problem-solving and communication skills.
Scripting experience (Python/JavaScript) and familiarity with Java/J2EE application environments.
ServiceNow Event Management experience desirable.
Why this role
Work on a mission-critical platform used nationwide, within an organisation committed to uplift in engineering excellence, service reliability and modern observability practices.

Recognised as one of the world’s largest IT and business consulting firms, CGI has offices across Australia, supporting local public and private sector clients to solve real business problems.  

We are looking to hire a Data Modeller who will focus on translating complex business requirements into clear, scalable, conceptual, logical, and physical data models that support analytics, reporting, and operational needs. Working closely with data engineers, analysts, and business stakeholders, the Data Modeller ensures that data is well-organized, standardized, and aligned with governance and quality frameworks to enable efficient data-driven decision-making across the organization.

Flexible work is available including hybrid work from client’s site at Port Melbourne  

Permanent and Fixed-Term Opportunities Available

Your future role and responsibilities:

Contribute to the design, development, and continuous refinement of conceptual, logical, and physical data models within the Data Transformation team.

Create and maintain SQL DDL scripts, along with detailed mapping and ETL documentation, to support Data Engineers in constructing and loading data models.

When required, carry out reverse engineering of existing data models from databases or SQL code to ensure alignment with current architecture and standards.

Develop and update business documentation, including process maps, taxonomies, and ontology diagrams, to provide clarity and traceability of data flows.

Maintain a strong emphasis on conceptual and business data modelling, ensuring that structures align with organisational objectives.

Interpret and translate business requirements into scalable data models that support long-term analytical and operational needs.

Assist in managing and maintaining controlled vocabularies and the corporate data catalogue to promote consistency and reuse of data assets.

Participate in modelling workshops and collaborative sessions with other Data Modellers to align on best practices and design approaches.

Adhere to existing Data Quality and Data Governance frameworks, contributing to their ongoing enhancement and ensuring compliance with modelling standards.

Build and maintain effective working relationships with subject matter experts and business stakeholders across the organisation.

Keep stakeholders and senior management informed of prioritisation decisions, project progress, and delivery timelines, managing expectations clearly and proactively.

Experience required to be successful in this role:

Sound understanding of data modelling methodologies, including Kimball, Inmon, Top-Sdown/Bottom-up, Relational and Dimensional Modelling, Data Warehousing, and 3NF approaches.

Ability to think conceptually and apply modelling techniques such as generalisation, subtyping, and super-typing to create efficient and flexible models.

Skilled in producing Entity Relationship Diagrams (ERDs) using a range of notations, such as Crow’s Foot and UML.

Strong technical understanding of databases, ETL/ELT pipelines, and programming languages (typically SQL), with the ability to connect these technologies to data modelling practices. (This is a hands-on role involving active work with data.)

Solid comprehension of business processes, with the ability to capture requirements accurately and translate them into effective technical designs.

Confident communicator, capable of engaging in technical discussions with both technical and non-technical audiences across all organisational levels.

Experience with cloud-based data technologies would be advantageous, particularly within the Microsoft Azure ecosystem, including:

Azure Data Lake

Azure Data Factory

Azure Databricks (SQL and Python)

Azure SQL Server

Azure DevOps / Git

At Intelligen, we’re building something different. In the past few years, we’ve grown from a bold idea into a trusted partner for some of Australia’s most complex data and AI transformations. We’ve helped enterprises modernise legacy platforms, embed data governance into decision-making, and bring responsible AI into real-world operations; all while scaling rapidly and purposefully.

As we deepen our footprint across Australia and APAC, we’re expanding our engineering capability in Sydney. We’re looking for a Software Engineer (Data Engineering Focus) who can design scalable architectures, build resilient data pipelines, and develop reliable software components that power analytics, governance, and AI initiatives.

If you thrive on solving big technical challenges, enjoy working across modern cloud ecosystems, and want to help build the next wave of intelligent data platforms, read on.

About the Role

This role centres on software engineering; designing, developing, testing and maintaining software applications, services and data processing systems across modern cloud environments. You will work closely with architects, engineers and client stakeholders to deliver robust, well-engineered solutions that integrate into larger enterprise platforms across Australia and the broader APAC region.

You’ll bring strong engineering fundamentals, deep data skills, and a collaborative mindset and you’ll be comfortable working across the full software and data lifecycle.



What You’ll Do
Design and implement scalable software architectures, APIs, and data processing frameworks tailored to complex business and technical requirements.
Build and optimise ETL/ELT pipelines, data ingestion frameworks, batch and streaming workloads using Python, SQL, and cloud-native technologies.
Engineer data solutions across modern data stacks including Snowflake, Databricks, Azure, AWS, GCP, Fabric,dbt, Coalesce, and more.
Develop, test, and maintain high-quality code with a focus on performance, reliability, and maintainability.
Implement CI/CD pipelines, automated testing, infrastructure-as-code, and environment configuration.
Identify and reduce software and data lifecycle risks such as performance bottlenecks, system failures, and integration issues.
Partner with product teams, analytics teams, governance specialists, and platform engineers to integrate solutions into broader architectures.
Support data governance, quality, metadata, and lineage practices within engineered systems.
Participate in solution design reviews, architectural discussions, and delivery planning sessions with clients.
Develop technical design documents, workflow diagrams, data dictionaries, runbooks, and developer/user guides.
Continuously monitor, debug, and optimise systems and pipelines for performance and operational excellence.
Contribute to engineering standards, reusable frameworks, and internal accelerators that uplift delivery across Intelligen.


Requirements



4+ years’ experience in software engineering, data engineering, or similar technical roles.
Strong proficiency in Python, SQL, and cloud-native development across Azure, AWS, and/or GCP.
Experience with modern data platforms such as Snowflake, Databricks, Fabric, dbt, Coalesce.
Strong understanding of ETL/ELT design, APIs, integration patterns, and distributed systems.
Exposure to analytics or BI tools (Power BI, Tableau) is advantageous.
Comfortable in a stakeholder-facing or consulting environment.
Excellent communication skills, able to clearly articulate technical concepts to a range of audiences.
Independent, self-driven, detail-oriented, and committed to continuous learning.



Benefits



We’re not just delivering AI and data projects - we’re humanising them. Curiosity, creativity, and impact matter to us as much as technical excellence. You’ll work with a team that values collaboration, diversity of thought, and bold ideas.

At Intelligen, you’ll have real influence on your projects, on our engineering practice, and on the future of responsible AI in Australia and the region. As we scale, so will your opportunity to grow, lead, and shape the direction of our capabilities.

If you’re ready to build meaningful systems, solve challenging problems, and help define the future of responsible AI and data engineering in Australia, we’d love to meet you.

Job Title: Senior Azure Cloud Customer Experience Engineer
Ad Text:
Overview


Microsoft’s mission is to empower every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more. As employees we come together with a growth mindset, innovate to empower others and collaborate to realize our shared goals. Each day we build on our values of respect, integrity, and accountability to create a culture of inclusion where everyone can thrive at work and beyond.

Every minute of every day, customers stake their entire business and reputation on Microsoft Cloud. The Azure Customer Experience (CXP) team believes that when we meet our high standards for quality and reliability, our customers win. If we falter, our customers fail their end-customers. Our vision is to turn Microsoft Cloud customers into fans.

We are the ACES Strategic team (Advanced Cloud Engineering & Supportability), a global engineering team in Azure CXP and we are focused on Strategic Azure Customers. We are customer-obsessed problem-solvers. We orchestrate and drive deep engagements in areas like Incident Management, Problem Management, Support, Resiliency, and empowering the customers. We represent the customer and amplify customer voice with Azure Engineering connecting to the quality vision for Azure. We innovate and find ways to scale our learning across our customer base. Diversity and inclusion are central to who we are, how we work, and what we enable our customers to achieve. We know that empowering our customers starts with empowering our team to show up authentically, work in ways that are best for them, and achieve their career goals.


Are you constantly customer-obsessed and passionate about solving complex technical problems? Do you take pride in enhancing customer experience through innovation? If the answer is Yes, then join us and surround yourself with people who are passionate about cloud computing and believe that extraordinary support is critical to customer success.

As a customer focused Advanced Cloud Engineer, you are the primary engineering contact accountable for your customer’s support experience on Azure. You will drive resolution of critical and complex problems, support key customer projects on Azure, and be the voice of the customer within Azure. In this role, you will work in partnership with Customer Success Account Managers, Cloud Solution Architects, Technical Support Engineers, and Azure engineering with our mission to turn Azure customers into fans with world-class engineering-led support experience.

Microsoft’s mission is to empower every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more. As employees we come together with a growth mindset, innovate to empower others and collaborate to realize our shared goals. Each day we build on our values of respect, integrity, and accountability to create a culture of inclusion where everyone can thrive at work and beyond.

Responsibilities

Technically Oriented

Track customer incidents, engage with strategic customers and partners to understand issues, contribute to troubleshooting through diagnostics, communicate progress and next steps to customers with a focus on reducing time taken to mitigate critical incidents.

Use engineering and support tools, customer telemetry and/or direct customer input to detect and flag trends/patterns of issues in the products or products misuse across customers. Develop and share insights and best practices with customers. 

Recommend and help develop training/readiness modules (e.g., mentoring, leading triages, content creation, brown bag sessions, blogs, quality assurance checks). Acts as a mentor, shares knowledge, and contributes to the content and readiness strategy for the team.

Customer Solution Lifecycle Management

Serve as a connecting point between the product team and customers throughout the engagement lifecycle, engage with customers to understand their business and availability needs, develop and offer proactive guidance on designing configurations and deploying solutions on Azure.

Handle complex escalations on customer issues from the customer or support or field teams, conduct impact analysis, help customers with answers to their technical questions, and serve as an escalation resource in areas of subject matter expertise.  

Conduct in-depth root cause analysis of issues and translates findings into opportunities for improvement and track and drive them as repair items.


Relationship/Experience Management 

Act as voice of customers and synthesize product feedback from strategic customers to provide input on business plans developed by the product groups. Identify customer usage patterns and drive resolutions on reoccurring issues with product groups. Close the feedback loop with the customers on product features.  

Partner with other teams (e.g., program managers, software engineers, product, customer service support teams), prioritize, unblock, and resolve critical customer issues.    

Collaborate with stakeholders to deliver solutions to strategic customers and develop mechanisms that improve customer health and reduce the turnover time.

Qualifications

Bachelor's Degree in Engineering, Computer Science, Information Technology (IT), Data Analytics/Science, Artificial Intelligence (AI), or related field AND 4+ years experience in technology industry, cloud, technical support, and/or customer experience engineering 

OR equivalent experience. 

4+ years of demonstrated experience supporting and troubleshooting enterprise level, mission-critical applications and infrastructure resolving complex issues/situations and driving technical resolution across cross-functional organizations.

2+ years of Experience with being on-call and driving mitigation for mission critical incidents.

The ability to meet Microsoft, customer and/or government security screening requirements are required for this role. These requirements include but are not limited to the following specialized security screenings: Microsoft Cloud Background Check: This position will be required to pass the Microsoft Cloud background check upon hire/transfer and every two years thereafter.

Technical Skills: Demonstrated hands-on experience with Subject Matter Expert level expertise in one or more of the following Cloud technologies:  

Core IaaS: Compute (Windows/Linux), Storage, Networking, Kubernetes, High Availability    

Data Platform and Bigdata: Azure SQL DB, Cosmos DB, PostgreSQL on Azure, Azure Data Bricks, Azure Data Factory, AI/ML  

Azure PaaS Services: App Services, Azure Functions, Redis Cache, and Event Hub.    

Monitoring technologies: Azure Monitor, Log Analytics, Grafana, Datadog, Confluent and similar technologies.    

Communication skills: ability to empathize with customers and convey confidence. Able to explain highly technical issues to varied audiences. Able to prioritize and advocate customer’s needs to the proper channels. Take ownership and work towards a resolution.    

Customer Obsession: Passion for customers and focus on delivering the right customer experience.

Growth Mindset: Openness and ability to learn new skills and technologies in a fast-paced environment.


This position will be open for a minimum of 5 days, with applications accepted on an ongoing basis until the position is filled.

Microsoft is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ancestry, citizenship, color, family or medical care leave, gender identity or expression, genetic information, immigration status, marital status, medical condition, national origin, physical or mental disability, political affiliation, protected veteran or military status, race, ethnicity, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, or any other characteristic protected by applicable local laws, regulations and ordinances. If you need assistance with religious accommodations and/or a reasonable accommodation due to a disability during the application process, read more about requesting accommodations.

Data Engineers


1x Data Engineer & 1x Senior Data Engineer with expertise in Microsoft Azure Data Platform required for NSW Government Department. Redfern + Parramatta + WFH. ASAP start; initial assignment until 30th June 2026.

Pay rate: Data Engineer: $1000 per day + super // Senior Data Engineer: $1100 per day + super
  
The ideal candidate is a hands-on engineer with strong problem-solving skills, solid architectural understanding, and proven experience building scalable, governed data and BI solutions to deliver reliable data models and meaningful business insights.
  
Key Responsibilities

Design and build scalable data models — design and develop well-structured facts, dimensions, and semantic layers using PySpark, Synapse, Fabric Lakehouse/Warehouse, and Power BI ensuring alignment with business and analytical requirements.
Develop ingestion and transformation pipelines — design and implement end-to-end data ingestion frameworks in Synapse Pipelines and Data Factory to source data from APIs, databases, and files. Build efficient ELT frameworks in Synapse and Fabric to integrate and transform large, complex datasets.
Design and deliver BI and analytics solutions — create Power BI models and reports that enable trusted analytics and actionable insights.
Optimise and govern — ensure high performance, cost efficiency, and data quality across Spark, SQL, and Fabric workloads through effective design and governance practices.
Collaborate and lead — partner with architects, analysts, and business stakeholders to design end-to-end data products, while mentoring engineers and promoting best practices in data design and delivery.
Selection Criteria:

5 years+ experience working in Analytics or data warehousing environments
Expert in data warehousing, data modelling, and end-to-end business intelligence solutions using Power BI, SQL, DAX.
Expert level knowledge in PySpark, SQL. Hands-on Synapse, Fabric (Spark + Pipelines)
Strong background in lakehouses, data platform frameworks and data mesh architecture
Experience with Azure DevOps, branching and pipelines
Experience delivering data solutions in projects with big data volumes
Experience applying AI/LLMs to data engineering (nice to have)
If you have the relevant skills and experience, please apply now with your up-to-date CV (in Word format).

Combat Systems Engineer Opportunities – Growing Our Maritime Engineering Team

As we expand our Maritime portfolio, we’re seeking multiple Combat Systems Engineers to join our growing team supporting multiple initiatives across Land, Surface, Subsurface, Air and Space domains. These roles contribute directly to the design, integration and delivery of advanced combat systems for the Australian Defence Force. 




About the Opportunities:

As part of our expanding Combat Systems Engineering team, you will contribute to systems engineering activities across the full lifecycle. Working within multidisciplinary teams, you will help shape mission-critical capabilities and ensure the successful delivery of complex naval systems.

You will:

Contribute to Combat System engineering activities including requirements analysis, architecture definition, subsystem development and preparation for integration and verification.

Support the hands-on management, development and refinement of Combat System architectures.

Develop, maintain and update functional and non-functional requirements, system models and design artefacts.

Support planning, development and execution of Verification activities and associated documentation.

Prepare for major program milestones including design reviews, test readiness reviews and system readiness reviews.

Develop and progress Engineering Changes through the engineering lifecycle.

Provide technical expertise and mentor junior engineers as needed.

Collaborate closely with specialty disciplines (Safety, Human Factors, Cyber, Topside, ILS) to ensure design assurance and holistic system compliance.

 

About You:

You’re a skilled Systems Engineer ready to contribute to high-profile Defence programs. You enjoy solving complex problems, collaborating in multidisciplinary environments, and driving engineering outcomes that make a real impact.

You bring:

Extensive experience across the systems engineering lifecycle, using structured methods, tools (including DOORS) and disciplined processes.

Strong background in the design and development of military systems incorporating GFX and COTS components.

Significant experience integrating, testing and evaluating Combat System products on naval platforms or similarly complex systems.

Experience working in a multi-disciplinary engineering environment, ideally within Defence.

Ability to engage effectively with internal stakeholders and external partners to achieve shared outcomes.

Deep expertise in relevant combat system technologies and domains.

Experience applying engineering development methodologies to complex systems.

Knowledge of key C4ISREW or warfare domains (AAW, ASW, ASuW) is highly regarded.

 

Why Join Us:
Gain unparalleled, hands-on proficiency through LMA’s comprehensive learning framework, which blends reach-back access to Lockheed Martin expertise with immersive training in Combat System Management and Integrated Weapon Systems. You’ll learn directly from local, multi-domain combat system integration specialists, benefiting from their real-world insights while developing a self-directed, “learn by doing” mindset.

You’ll also have access to LMA’s extensive online technical library, including curated instructional courseware, the Engineering Storefront for on-demand learning modules, pre-recorded webinars, and active participation in LMA’s electronic forums. Together, these resources are designed to help you deepen your knowledge, solve complex integration challenges, and stay well ahead-of-ready in the naval surface combatant domain.


How we reward and support you: 

When you join Lockheed Martin, you work on projects you won’t experience anywhere else.

We offer you a range of benefits built to suit you, no matter what stage of life you are in. 

Flexible work & Hybrid work options

Access to our online discounts program offering immediate discounts or cashback

A variety of leave options including Purchase Leave to support you and your family  

Additional benefits such as Annual Flu Vaccinations, Novated Leasing and Fitness Programs

Job ID: 174718

 

Employment Type: Full time

About the role

As part of the Digital First program, the Unified Data View (UDV) will provide a complete, accurate, and up-to-date data for Business Intelligence, data analysis, and enhanced collection search capability.

The Unified Data View aggregates, unifies and presents collection metadata from multiple, disparate sources into a single, cohesive view to facilitate better decision making, improve data accessibility, and enhance data analysis capabilities for staff across the National Archives of Australia. The underpinning technologies are based on Microsoft cloud technologies, including Microsoft Fabric OneLake data warehouse, Power BI business intelligence and Microsoft Azure Application Programming Interface Management (APIM).

To sustain, maintain and further develop these new technologies, Technology Branch have a vacancy for an EL1 Data Engineer to manage ongoing operations of the Unified Data View.

Under limited direction, the main duties of the role are to:           

Lead and manage the team responsible for delivery of the Unified Data View.

Oversee the sustainment and development of the unified data warehouse and associated data engineering solutions.

Design and implement complex ETL data flows to integrate collection system data into the warehouse, enabling the creation of business intelligence products while ensuring robust data security and governance.

Manage data warehouse architecture and configuration, establish standardised data modelling guidelines, and implement industry best practices.

Define and enforce data quality standards, processes, and controls, continuously monitoring data quality and integrity, and addressing issues promptly to ensure reliability.

Collaborate with stakeholders to identify and prioritise data sets for ingestion into the warehouse, aligning with current and future business reporting requirements.

Maintain, or ability to gain, skills in database fundamentals, Python and Power BI, Microsoft Azure SQL, Azure DevOps and MS Fabric. Relevant certifications or equivalent qualifications would be well regarded.

Perform detailed analyses on data and business processes, translating business needs into actionable and effective data solutions.

Support the Unified Data View’s self-service function for the wider National Archive users.

Lead the development and enhancement of data engineering frameworks and best practices, focusing on optimising the availability, security, and performance of data assets and maintenance of data pipelines.

Apply the principles of APS Values, Code of Conduct, workplace diversity principles, work health and safety and participative management within a work and team environment.

Promote and apply the National Archives’ Vision, Mission and Commitments as expressed in in Strategy 2025–2030: Evolving National Archives and Our Values

Who we are

National Archives provides leadership in the best practice management of the official record of the Commonwealth and ensures that Australia Government information of enduring significance is secured, preserved and available to government agencies, researchers and the community.

Our vision: Australia’s cultural identity and democracy are strengthened by connecting people with the evidence of Australian Government activities and decisions.

We operate in a complex, challenging and changing environment requiring professional and robust risk management. We support a positive risk culture where risks are discussed regularly and either accepted or actively managed to prevent or reduce their impact. National Archives recognises that the factors that generate risks can also create opportunities, particularly in our rapidly changing digital environment.

National Archives is committed to:

innovation

collaboration

inclusion

National Archives is also committed to developing the capability and expertise of our staff, we offer a Studies Assistance Program that supports staff to achieve individual goals as well as increasing their capacity to help achieve National Archives’ strategic objectives. Our Health and Wellbeing program encourages and supports a healthier workplace and healthy lifestyle changes for employees.

Are you eligible?

To be eligible for the role you must be an Australian citizen. If you are selected, you will be required to successfully undergo a pre-employment check and be able to obtain and maintain a security clearance at a Baseline clearance level.

How to apply

You need to apply through our e-recruitment system.

Your application will need to include:

the names and contact details of at least two referees, one of whom should be a current supervisor.

your current resume (maximum 3 pages).

statement (maximum 1000 words) describing how your skills, knowledge, and experience/qualifications would enable you to perform the duties of the role taking into account the “Performance Expectations” at the relevant classification and the National Archives’ Vision, Mission and Commitments as expressed in Strategy 2025–2030: Evolving National Archives and Our Values.
